{
  "texts": [
    "Intuitively, TIES preserves the relevant task updates while filtering out contradictory ones.",
    "Model Stock.",
    "Model Stock (Jang et al., 2024) moves the merged weights toward the geometric center of a set of fine-tuned checkpoints: given pre-trained weights W 0 and fine-tuned checkpoints {W i } N i=1, Model Stock selects the point that is geometrically closest to the unknown center, i.e.",
    "the true geometric midpoint of the shell that the checkpoints would define in weight space by a layerwise interpolation between W 0 and the average of the fine-tuned variants (W avg).",
    "Mathematically, the method computes the merged model as"
  ]
}